tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild erythrocytopenia and low hematocrit, but hemoglobin is slightly elevated, possibly due to hemoconcentration. Leukocytes and platelets are within normal limits, though platelet distribution width is markedly increased, which may indicate platelet anisocytosis. No acute hematological abnormality is evident, but findings may suggest mild anemia; clinical correlation and further evaluation are recommended.
